id: pm-u14c
title: "As an organization running thousands of agents, I can verify which principal recorded each history entry: per-entry author signatures complementing hash-chain tamper-evidence"
description: Explore per-entry cryptographic author signatures and key-management models that add verifiable authorship to existing hash-chain tamper evidence at fleet scale.
type: Story
status: open
priority: 4
tags[5]: exploration,history,identity,integrity,long-horizon
created_at: "2026-07-06T23:35:58.629Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-22T18:26:39.932Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: "Spike + ADR only at this stage: a written exploration evaluates per-entry signature schemes (author keypairs, git-commit-signing reuse, workspace trust store), key distribution/rotation for thousands of agent principals, verify integration into the existing history --verify path, storage/token overhead per entry, and opt-in configuration; the ADR states an accept/defer decision with scale measurements from the pm-mi2x workspaces; no implementation lands before the ADR is accepted"
parent: pm-o2kc
risk: low
confidence: medium
